Package com.serena.dmclient.api Description

This package provides classes and interfaces for querying, updating, creating, and deleting Dimensions CM objects such as item revisions and requests.

These classes are capable of easily and efficiently handling anything that a Dimensions CM client might need to do. This package contains four main groups of classes and interfaces:

  • Classes for Dimensions CM connection management.
  • Classes for creating new Dimensions CM objects.
  • Classes for operating on existing Dimensions CM objects.
  • Classes for operating on administrative Dimensions CM objects.
Note that there are two related packages, com.serena.dmclient.objects and com.serena.dmclient.collections, which provide additional administrative Dimensions CM functionality.

Details

Connection management refers to opening, closing, and keeping track of connections to the Dimensions CM server. The DimensionsConnectionManager class serves as the main entry point for this functionality.

Creating new Dimensions CM objects refers to the registration of new business data into the Dimensions CM server and database. The DimensionsObjectFactory interface serves as the main entry point for this functionality, and has methods for retrieving existing business data in the form of DimensionsObject instances.

Operating on existing Dimensions CM objects refers to updating the business data currently registered in the Dimensions CM server and database. For example, updating the attributes or relationships between that data. The DimensionsObject interface is the base interface for the interfaces that provide this functionality. Bulk operations are performed using the BulkOperator interface that can be obtained using DimensionsObjectFactory.getBulkOperator(List).

Operating on administrative Dimensions CM objects refers to updating the process model data currently registered in the Dimensions database. For example, defining a new request type and creating and assigning a new lifecycle to it. The entry point for these functions is the DimensionsDatabaseAdmin object, a reference to which may be obtained by a call to DimensionsObjectFactory.getBaseDatabaseAdmin(). For the Dimensions CM 10.1 release, several changes have occurred to the locations of classes and interfaces that were published in the pre-Dimensions CM 10.1 dmpmcli Javadoc:

  • Interfaces that were in the com.merant.dimensions.objects package now reside in the com.serena.dmclient.objects package.
  • Public classes that were in the com.merant.dimensions.objects package now reside in the com.serena.dmclient.objects package.
  • Interfaces that were in the com.merant.dimensions.collections package now reside in the com.serena.dmclient.collections package.
For more details and to see how your legacy dmpmcli scripts might be affected, see the com.serena.dmclient.objects package documentation.

Package Specification

(none)

Implementation Notes

This API and dmpmcli.jar both require JDK 1.4.2 as a minimum. The JAR files work with JDK 1.4 and JDK 1.5 without changes.

Related Documentation

The following classes and interfaces from the com.serena.dmclient.objects package are used by the com.serena.dmclient.api package.
  • DimensionsObject
  • DimensionsObjectDetails
  • DimensionsDatabaseAdmin
  • RequestType
There may be others as this is not an exhaustive list.
